race.comment: THINKING GOLD (7) was handy on straightening and finished a brave runner-up when resuming over 1600m at Pakenham, beaten by less than a length. He shows plenty of talent and looks hard to beat in this suitable race. ITSUKUSHIMA (3) is knocking on the door, placing in his last two starts, including a close second over 1600m at Werribee, beaten by just under a length. He should settle just off the pace and can go one better. CLAVEL (9) was unplaced first-up and then again last time out when ninth over 1400m at Cranbourne just over 3 weeks ago. He slides down in class here and could bounce back to some worthwhile form. SINISTER SAUCE (18) has made an encouraging start to her season, and she should be fighting out the finish again. BANCORY BAY (1) dips in grade here and can find some form again. Each way value.
